Parliament, Thursday, 11 June 2020 – The Portfolio Committee on Public Enterprises and the Select Committee on Public Enterprises and Communications express their heartfelt condolences to the family of Ms Dorah Dlamini on her passing.
	
	Ms Dlamini was a member of the Portfolio Committee on Public Enterprises.
	
	Committee Chairpersons Mr Khaya Magaxa and Mr Tshitereke Matibe said their committees are deeply saddened to learn of her passing. Ms Dlamini was a committed and dedicated public representative, who served Parliament and the committee until her very last day.
	
	The committees send their thoughts and prayers to the Dlamini family during this difficult time.
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON PUBLIC ENTERPRISES, MR KHAYA MAGAXA, AND THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE SELECT COMMITTEE ON PUBLIC ENTERPRISES AND COMMUNICATIONS, MR TSHITEREKE MATIBE
	
